    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@JanSchulz - just about, thanks!\n\nI don't think there needs to be more than one (or maybe two) configurables on the engine side:\n1. The only configurable we need seems to be `max_heartbeat_misses`, an integer for the number of HeartMonitor.periods for the interval we check.  When this is zero, checking is disabled.  That would seem to cover things pretty well.\n2. I wouldn't object to a separate `exit_on_missed_heartbeats` boolean flag, if explicit disable is preferable, but my leaning is ever-so-slightly towards a single configurable, but you are the author here, so I will defer to you on that.\n"
  },
