    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I'm not really opposed to it, but right now the default is the same as before the change, so no \"user visible\" change on upgrade (0 = no monitoring and therefore no killing the engine on missed heartbeats). If the option is set to 10, just upgrading will result in different behavior (\"oups, why is my engine dying when I restart my hub?\"), as the new option will not be present in the config files.\n\n-> Do a user visible default change or  not?\n\nI'm not familiar with the ipython policy on that matter, so it's your call :-)\n"
